Pao de Queio (brazilian Cheese Bread)

1 c whole milk
1 tsp salt
1 stick unsalted butter
2 c tapioca flour
2 eggs
2 g finely grated parmesan cheese, divided.

Preheat oven to 400F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. In a medium saucepan, combine the milk, salt, and butter, and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and whisk in the flour until incorporated. Transfer the mixture to a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. With the motor running on low speed, add eggs, one at a time, until incorporated, followed byt 1 1/2 c of cheese. Scoop 2 tbsp size balls of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spaced 1" apart. Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the balls of dough. Bake until golden brown and puffed, 20-25min. Remove from the oven and transfer to a platter. Serve warm.
